, 
<figureCitation box="[820,856,471,497]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="17.[189,232,1822,1848]" captionTargetBox="[289,1298,265,1783]" captionTargetId="figure-11@17.[289,1298,265,1783]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Fig. 8. Dexosarcophaga spp., ♂ and ♀, habitus and terminalia. A. Dexosarcophaga petra sp. nov., ♂, paratype (MNRJ [lost]), Brazil, Mato Grosso, Chapada dos Guimarães, terminalia, lateral view. B–D. Dexosarcophaga sphaera sp. nov., paratypes (MNRJ [lost]), Brazil, Brasília, Distrito Federal, Fazenda Vargem Bonita. B. ♂, habitus, lateral view. C. ♂, terminalia, lateral view. D. ♀, terminalia, ventral view. E–F. Dexosarcophaga napo sp. nov., ♂, paratype (NHRS [lost]), Ecuador, Napo Prov. E. Habitus, lateral view. F. Terminalia, lateral view. Scale bars =1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6823748" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6823748/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="123">8A</figureCitation>
