<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="123" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="14.[189,335,1254,1280]" box="[189,335,1254,1280]" pageId="14" pageNumber="123">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,335,1254,1280]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="14" pageNumber="123" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,335,1254,1280]" pageId="14" pageNumber="123">Description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[189,930,1301,1363]" box="[234,378,1301,1328]" pageId="14" pageNumber="123">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[234,298,1301,1327]" pageId="14" pageNumber="123">Male</emphasis>
(n=3)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[189,930,1301,1363]" box="[189,930,1336,1363]" pageId="14" pageNumber="123">
Length: 
<quantity box="[288,401,1337,1363]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" metricValueMax="11.0" metricValueMin="7.0" pageId="14" pageNumber="123" unit="mm" value="9.0" valueMax="11.0" valueMin="7.0">7–11 mm</quantity>
. Differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="Santos &amp; Pape &amp; Mello-Patiu, 2022" authorityName="Santos &amp; Pape &amp; Mello-Patiu" authorityYear="2022" box="[567,697,1336,1362]" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Dexosarcophaga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phoenix" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[567,697,1336,1362]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="123">D. phoenix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[704,795,1337,1363]" pageId="14" pageNumber="123" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
as follows:
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[188,1400,1402,1815]" pageId="14" pageNumber="123">
Frons about 0.18 × head width at level of ocellar triangle; 9–12 well-developed frontal setae reaching level of apex of pedicel; gena and genal groove with slightly yellowish-silver pollinosity; intra-alars 2+ 2; meral setae 7–9; scutellum with pair of reduced apical setae; T4 with 1–2 pairs of lateral marginal setae; row of about 10 marginal setae on T5; arms of ST5 about half of basal length and inner margin with distinctly projected lobes (
<figureCitation box="[575,672,1543,1569]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="15.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[242,1359,273,1826]" captionTargetId="figure-11@15.[213,1374,265,1854]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Fig. 7. Dexosarcophaga petra sp. nov., ♂, paratype (MNRJ [lost]), Brazil, Rio de Janeiro, Angra dos Reis. A. Sternite 5, ventral view. B. Syntergosternite 7+ 8, epandrium, cercus and surstylus, lateral view. C. Cerci, posterior view. D. Phallus and associated structures, lateral view. E. Distiphallus, ventral view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods. Scale bars =0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6823746" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6823746/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="123">Fig. 7A</figureCitation>
); cercus with apical half curved anteriorly (
<figureCitation box="[1207,1302,1543,1569]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="15.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[242,1359,273,1826]" captionTargetId="figure-11@15.[213,1374,265,1854]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Fig. 7. Dexosarcophaga petra sp. nov., ♂, paratype (MNRJ [lost]), Brazil, Rio de Janeiro, Angra dos Reis. A. Sternite 5, ventral view. B. Syntergosternite 7+ 8, epandrium, cercus and surstylus, lateral view. C. Cerci, posterior view. D. Phallus and associated structures, lateral view. E. Distiphallus, ventral view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods. Scale bars =0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6823746" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6823746/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="123">Fig. 7B</figureCitation>
); cercal prong rounded (
<figureCitation box="[385,518,1578,1604]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="15.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[242,1359,273,1826]" captionTargetId="figure-11@15.[213,1374,265,1854]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Fig. 7. Dexosarcophaga petra sp. nov., ♂, paratype (MNRJ [lost]), Brazil, Rio de Janeiro, Angra dos Reis. A. Sternite 5, ventral view. B. Syntergosternite 7+ 8, epandrium, cercus and surstylus, lateral view. C. Cerci, posterior view. D. Phallus and associated structures, lateral view. E. Distiphallus, ventral view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods. Scale bars =0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6823746" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6823746/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="123">Fig. 7B–C</figureCitation>
); surstylus narrow, with long setae in apical half (
<figureCitation box="[1138,1235,1578,1604]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="15.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[242,1359,273,1826]" captionTargetId="figure-11@15.[213,1374,265,1854]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Fig. 7. Dexosarcophaga petra sp. nov., ♂, paratype (MNRJ [lost]), Brazil, Rio de Janeiro, Angra dos Reis. A. Sternite 5, ventral view. B. Syntergosternite 7+ 8, epandrium, cercus and surstylus, lateral view. C. Cerci, posterior view. D. Phallus and associated structures, lateral view. E. Distiphallus, ventral view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods. Scale bars =0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6823746" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6823746/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="123">Fig. 7B</figureCitation>
); vesica with membranous and sclerotized areas, rounded in lateral view with apical projection, rectangular in ventral view with two projections in proximal part and two thorny projections in distal part (
<figureCitation box="[1190,1319,1648,1674]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="15.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[242,1359,273,1826]" captionTargetId="figure-11@15.[213,1374,265,1854]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Fig. 7. Dexosarcophaga petra sp. nov., ♂, paratype (MNRJ [lost]), Brazil, Rio de Janeiro, Angra dos Reis. A. Sternite 5, ventral view. B. Syntergosternite 7+ 8, epandrium, cercus and surstylus, lateral view. C. Cerci, posterior view. D. Phallus and associated structures, lateral view. E. Distiphallus, ventral view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods. Scale bars =0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6823746" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6823746/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="123">Fig. 7D–E</figureCitation>
); juxta membranous and with spines proximally (
<figureCitation box="[681,809,1683,1710]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="15.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[242,1359,273,1826]" captionTargetId="figure-11@15.[213,1374,265,1854]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Fig. 7. Dexosarcophaga petra sp. nov., ♂, paratype (MNRJ [lost]), Brazil, Rio de Janeiro, Angra dos Reis. A. Sternite 5, ventral view. B. Syntergosternite 7+ 8, epandrium, cercus and surstylus, lateral view. C. Cerci, posterior view. D. Phallus and associated structures, lateral view. E. Distiphallus, ventral view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods. Scale bars =0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6823746" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6823746/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="123">Fig. 7D–E</figureCitation>
); median stylus narrow, with apical spines, shorter than lateral stylus and with base expanded towards ventral and dorsal margins of paraphallus (
<figureCitation captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="15.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[242,1359,273,1826]" captionTargetId="figure-11@15.[213,1374,265,1854]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Fig. 7. Dexosarcophaga petra sp. nov., ♂, paratype (MNRJ [lost]), Brazil, Rio de Janeiro, Angra dos Reis. A. Sternite 5, ventral view. B. Syntergosternite 7+ 8, epandrium, cercus and surstylus, lateral view. C. Cerci, posterior view. D. Phallus and associated structures, lateral view. E. Distiphallus, ventral view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods. Scale bars =0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6823746" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6823746/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="123">Fig. 7D– E</figureCitation>
); lateral stylus narrow, base twisted towards ventral margin of paraphallus and with apical spines (
<figureCitation box="[198,326,1789,1815]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="15.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[242,1359,273,1826]" captionTargetId="figure-11@15.[213,1374,265,1854]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Fig. 7. Dexosarcophaga petra sp. nov., ♂, paratype (MNRJ [lost]), Brazil, Rio de Janeiro, Angra dos Reis. A. Sternite 5, ventral view. B. Syntergosternite 7+ 8, epandrium, cercus and surstylus, lateral view. C. Cerci, posterior view. D. Phallus and associated structures, lateral view. E. Distiphallus, ventral view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods. Scale bars =0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6823746" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6823746/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="123">Fig. 7D–E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
