<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="125" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="16.[189,304,377,403]" box="[189,304,377,403]" pageId="16" pageNumber="125">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,304,377,403]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="16" pageNumber="125" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,304,377,403]" pageId="16" pageNumber="125">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[189,1400,423,1153]" pageId="16" pageNumber="125">
<taxonomicName authority="Santos &amp; Pape &amp; Mello-Patiu, 2022" authorityName="Santos &amp; Pape &amp; Mello-Patiu" authorityYear="2022" box="[189,461,423,449]" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Dexosarcophaga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="petra" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[189,461,423,449]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="125">Dexosarcophaga petra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[469,559,424,450]" pageId="16" pageNumber="125" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is morphologically similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Santos &amp; Pape &amp; Mello-Patiu, 2022" authorityName="Santos &amp; Pape &amp; Mello-Patiu" authorityYear="2022" box="[914,1017,423,449]" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Dexosarcophaga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="limon" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[914,1017,423,449]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="125">D. limon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1026,1117,424,450]" pageId="16" pageNumber="125" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(see remarks under that species). There are also similarities with 
<taxonomicName authority="Dodge, 1968" authorityName="Dodge" authorityYear="1968" box="[683,986,458,484]" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Dexosarcophaga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="malaisei">
<emphasis box="[683,822,458,484]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="125">D. malaisei</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Dodge H. R." box="[832,986,458,484]" pageId="16" pageNumber="125" pagination="421 - 450" refId="ref10829" refString="Dodge H. R. 1968. The Sarcophagidae of Barro Colorado Island, Panama (Diptera). Annals of the Entomological Society of America 61: 421 - 450. https: // doi. org / 10.1093 / aesa / 61.2.421" type="journal article" year="1968">Dodge, 1968</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="De-Souza, Souza, Soares &amp; Carvalho-Filho, 2020" authorityName="De-Souza, Souza, Soares &amp; Carvalho-Filho" authorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Dexosarcophaga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="salgada">
<emphasis box="[1047,1180,458,484]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="125">D. salgada</emphasis>
De-Souza, Souza, Soares &amp; Carvalho-Filho, 2020
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="De-Souza C. C. &amp; Souza M. T. &amp; Soares J. M. &amp; Carvalho-Filho F. D. S." box="[576,830,493,520]" pageId="16" pageNumber="125" pagination="267 - 273" refId="ref10747" refString="De-Souza C. C., Souza M. T., Soares J. M. &amp; Carvalho-Filho F. D. S. 2021. Description of two new species of Dexosarcophaga (Diptera: Sarcophagidae) from the coastal environments of the Brazilian Amazon. Journal of Medical entomology 58: 267 - 273. [Published online 17 September 2020; printed January 2021] https: // doi. org / 10.1093 / jme / tjaa 177" type="journal article" year="2021">
De-Souza 
<emphasis box="[700,760,493,519]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="125">et al.</emphasis>
2021
</bibRefCitation>
). Males of these species have cercus curved and vesica mostly rounded. 
<bibRefCitation author="Lopes H. S." box="[475,648,528,555]" pageId="16" pageNumber="125" pagination="511 - 522" refId="ref11187" refString="Lopes H. S. 1975 c. On the types of some species of Sarcophagidae from Panama, described by H. R. Dodge (Diptera). Revista Brasileira de Biologia 34: 511 - 522." type="journal article" year="1975">Lopes (1975c)</bibRefCitation>
reviewed the morphology of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dodge" authorityYear="1968" box="[1009,1146,529,555]" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Dexosarcophaga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="malaisei">
<emphasis box="[1009,1146,529,555]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="125">D. malaisei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and commented that the terminalia of the 
<typeStatus box="[448,551,564,590]" pageId="16" pageNumber="125">holotype</typeStatus>
were lost apart from syntergosternite 7+8 (= “first genital segment”). However, since the species does not have 
<typeStatus box="[705,817,600,626]" pageId="16" pageNumber="125">paratypes</typeStatus>
and the illustrations of the phallus provided by 
<bibRefCitation author="Dodge H. R." box="[189,349,634,660]" pageId="16" pageNumber="125" pagination="421 - 450" refId="ref10829" refString="Dodge H. R. 1968. The Sarcophagidae of Barro Colorado Island, Panama (Diptera). Annals of the Entomological Society of America 61: 421 - 450. https: // doi. org / 10.1093 / aesa / 61.2.421" type="journal article" year="1968">Dodge (1968</bibRefCitation>
: figs 17–18) are sketchy and insufficient for recognizing 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dodge" authorityYear="1968" box="[1029,1167,634,660]" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Dexosarcophaga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="malaisei">
<emphasis box="[1029,1167,634,660]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="125">D. malaisei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, we cannot make a detailed morphological comparison between these three nominal species. Consequently, either 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Santos &amp; Pape &amp; Mello-Patiu" authorityYear="2022" box="[1301,1398,670,695]" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Dexosarcophaga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="petra">
<emphasis box="[1301,1398,670,695]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="125">D. petra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName authorityName="De-Souza, Souza, Soares &amp; Carvalho-Filho" authorityYear="2020" box="[221,349,705,731]" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Dexosarcophaga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="salgada">
<emphasis box="[221,349,705,731]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="125">D. salgada</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
could be a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dodge" authorityYear="1968" box="[708,844,705,731]" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Dexosarcophaga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="malaisei">
<emphasis box="[708,844,705,731]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="125">D. malaisei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but we will here rely particularly on the shape of the male pregonite and cercus as illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Dodge H. R." box="[766,924,740,766]" pageId="16" pageNumber="125" pagination="421 - 450" refId="ref10829" refString="Dodge H. R. 1968. The Sarcophagidae of Barro Colorado Island, Panama (Diptera). Annals of the Entomological Society of America 61: 421 - 450. https: // doi. org / 10.1093 / aesa / 61.2.421" type="journal article" year="1968">Dodge (1968</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 17). The evenly curved or C-shaped pregonite and the cercus that is straight over most of its length and curved in the distal fourth appear sufficiently different from both 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Santos &amp; Pape &amp; Mello-Patiu" authorityYear="2022" box="[569,671,811,836]" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Dexosarcophaga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="petra">
<emphasis box="[569,671,811,836]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="125">D. petra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(pregonite with middle part straight; cercus bent rather than curved) and from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="De-Souza, Souza, Soares &amp; Carvalho-Filho" authorityYear="2020" box="[409,542,845,871]" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Dexosarcophaga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="salgada">
<emphasis box="[409,542,845,871]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="125">D. salgada</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(pregonite with only distal part curved; cercus evenly curved) to reject conspecificity. Therefore, we consider 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Santos &amp; Pape &amp; Mello-Patiu" authorityYear="2022" box="[653,755,881,906]" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Dexosarcophaga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="petra">
<emphasis box="[653,755,881,906]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="125">D. petra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="De-Souza, Souza, Soares &amp; Carvalho-Filho" authorityYear="2020" box="[818,950,881,907]" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Dexosarcophaga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="salgada">
<emphasis box="[818,950,881,907]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="125">D. salgada</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as valid nominal species until future studies produce material from the type locality of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dodge" authorityYear="1968" box="[776,912,916,942]" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Dexosarcophaga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="malaisei">
<emphasis box="[776,912,916,942]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="125">D. malaisei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(i.e., Barro Colorado, 
<collectingCountry box="[1178,1276,916,942]" name="Panama" pageId="16" pageNumber="125">Panama</collectingCountry>
), allowing a better resolution of this question. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Santos &amp; Pape &amp; Mello-Patiu" authorityYear="2022" box="[626,901,951,977]" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Dexosarcophaga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="petra">
<emphasis box="[626,901,951,977]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="125">Dexosarcophaga petra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="De-Souza, Souza, Soares &amp; Carvalho-Filho" authorityYear="2020" box="[965,1099,951,977]" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Dexosarcophaga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="salgada">
<emphasis box="[965,1099,951,977]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="125">D. salgada</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be separated by the following differences in the shape of the vesica in particular: broadest proximally (lateral view), with broad median fissure, without median knob-like projections and with an apical projection in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[262,354,1057,1083]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="15.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[242,1359,273,1826]" captionTargetId="figure-11@15.[213,1374,265,1854]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Fig. 7. Dexosarcophaga petra sp. nov., ♂, paratype (MNRJ [lost]), Brazil, Rio de Janeiro, Angra dos Reis. A. Sternite 5, ventral view. B. Syntergosternite 7+ 8, epandrium, cercus and surstylus, lateral view. C. Cerci, posterior view. D. Phallus and associated structures, lateral view. E. Distiphallus, ventral view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods. Scale bars =0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6823746" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6823746/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="125">Fig. 7D</figureCitation>
) in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Santos &amp; Pape &amp; Mello-Patiu" authorityYear="2022" box="[398,497,1057,1082]" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Dexosarcophaga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="petra">
<emphasis box="[398,497,1057,1082]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="125">D. petra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, versus broadest distally, with narrow median fissure, a pair of median knoblike projections and without an apical projection in lateral view in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="De-Souza, Souza, Soares &amp; Carvalho-Filho" authorityYear="2020" box="[989,1121,1092,1118]" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Dexosarcophaga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="125" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="salgada">
<emphasis box="[989,1121,1092,1118]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="125">D. salgada</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="De-Souza C. C. &amp; Souza M. T. &amp; Soares J. M. &amp; Carvalho-Filho F. D. S." box="[1136,1395,1092,1118]" pageId="16" pageNumber="125" pagination="267 - 273" refId="ref10747" refString="De-Souza C. C., Souza M. T., Soares J. M. &amp; Carvalho-Filho F. D. S. 2021. Description of two new species of Dexosarcophaga (Diptera: Sarcophagidae) from the coastal environments of the Brazilian Amazon. Journal of Medical entomology 58: 267 - 273. [Published online 17 September 2020; printed January 2021] https: // doi. org / 10.1093 / jme / tjaa 177" type="journal article" year="2021">
De-Souza 
<emphasis box="[1264,1324,1092,1118]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="125">et al.</emphasis>
2021
</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 
<quantity box="[236,266,1127,1153]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="3.0" pageId="16" pageNumber="125" unit="g" value="3.0">3g</quantity>
–i).
</paragraph>
